data.title: We Asked ChatGPT To List the 20 Top Louisville Artists
data.meta_description: Don't shoot the messenger... We got bored and asked ChatGPT to list the top 20 artists from Louisville, and here's what it spit out for us.
data.text:
Don’t shoot the messenger… We got bored and asked ChatGPT to list the top 20 artists from Louisville, and here’s what it spit out for us:

My Morning Jacket – Indie rock band formed in 1998.

Jack Harlow – Hip hop artist and rapper.

Lionel Hampton – Jazz vibraphonist, pianist, percussionist, and bandleader.

Bryson Tiller – R&B singer, rapper, and songwriter.

Nappy Roots – Hip hop group formed in 1995.

Wax Fang – Psychedelic rock band formed in 2005.

Bonnie “Prince” Billy – Indie folk singer-songwriter.

Dave Moisan – Singer-songwriter and guitarist.

Slint – Post-rock band formed in 1986.

Joan Osborne – Singer-songwriter.

Houndmouth – Indie rock band formed in 2011.

The Villebillies – Hip hop group formed in 1998.

Squirrel Bait – Punk rock band formed in 1983.

White Reaper – Indie rock band formed in 2014.

King Kong – Experimental rock band formed in 1989.

Nerves Junior – Indie rock band formed in 2010.

Evergreen – Alternative rock band formed in 1994.

Your Black Star – Hip hop group formed in 2005.

Wax Factory – Hard rock band formed in 1993.

Lucky Pineapple – Indie rock band formed in 1997.

What do you think of the list? Any surprises? Any that are ranked too high or too low?
